<br>
<br>
1) make harvest a level 24 spell that gives 300 mana for a 12 second stun and add <br>
HARVEST II at level 44 (600 mana for 24 second stun)<br>
HARVEST III at level 60 (1200 mana for 48 second stun)<br>
with recast time of 10, 15, and 20 minutes respectively<br>
<br>
2) create a spell line something like &quot;Al'Kabors Lure of fire and Ice&quot;. Similar to enchanter Tash line but for fire/cold resists. (finally a useful Al'Kabor line)<br>
level 4 - single target lower resist to fire/cold by 10<br>
level 20 - single target lower resist to fire/cold by 20<br>
level 39 - single target lower resist to fire/cold by 30<br>
level 54 - single target lower resist to fire/cold by 40<br>
level 60 - Area Effect lower resist to fire/cold by 40<br>
<br>
3) minor familiar becomes a level 16 spell<br>
    lesser familiar becomes a level 29 spell<br>
    Familiar becomes a level 49 spell<br>
    Greater Familiar becomes a level 54 spell<br>
ADD Superior Familiar at 60  <br>
          *increase mana regen by 6<br>
          *increase mana by 225<br>
          *Reduce chance of Fizzle<br>
          * +35 to all saves<br>
*ALL FAMILIARS WILL BE GROUP BUFFS*<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats it! Thats all we need! These would make use much more effiecient both solo and in groups. And also would make use more wanted in groups at low to high levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/15/02 3:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take on improving Wizards without unbalancing</span><hr size=1> 15 mana per tick self regen (that is what your harvests add up to, and you can mem all 3).<br>
<br>
6 mana per tick group regen.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
Mate, that's ALOT of mana regen you are sticking onto the wizard class.<br>
<br>
Whatdoes that do to the wizards damage over time in a group?  Solo?  Which does it help more?<br>
<br>
How does it compare to monk rogue and mage damage over time?<br>
<br>
Should wizards do more damage on 1 target over time than monks/rogues?<br>
<br>
Balance is hard.  Buffing a class is easy.<br>
