The harvests would NOT stack, When you cast one, all 3 (if all were memmed) would grey out.<br>
<br>
They would be upgrades to the previuos spell, so this wouldnt give nearly the mana regen you were thinking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/16/02 3:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Aelvion, they can't do that with the current engine (all 3 gems greying out).<br>
<br>
There are 2 delay timers attached to spells:<br>
<br>
recast delay (time before the spell can be cast again, also time before the spell can be cast after memorization).<br>
<br>
recovery delay (time before you can cast ANY spell).<br>
<br>
It might be nice to have recast delays for entire lines, but balancing a wizard using non-implemented features in the game isn't the ideal route.  =)<br>
